            <div type="translation">
                <p>The purchase of the tomb. Palladios, the spouse of Pelagia. Pelagia having passed 11 [days] before the Kalends of [...], having died [...] of September, here she, who had one husband, lies</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p><!--commented out pending revision-->
                    <!--right side of an incomplete funerary inscription perhaps recording a Palladios and a Pelagia, died in the month of september. Kaible connects physically with 530a, although this appears to be based on an over literal reading of the layout of Gualtherus no.40 and no.41--></p>
            </div>
